import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.scatterplot(x='temperature', y='pressure', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between temperature and pressure?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='temperature', color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['temperature'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['temperature'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'month']).mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temperature', data=data, ax=ax, label='Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='pressure', data=data, ax=ax, label='Pressure')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='wind', data=data, ax=ax, label='Wind')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average temperature, pressure, and wind speed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
